  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">KKT Actions to reduce health risks and strengthen IDPs and communities&#x2019; resilience in accessin</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will address the escalated health risks due to COVID-19 pandemic and preparedness of most vulnerable and critically affected ethnic minorities and Internally displaced population (IDPs) living in most fragile and hard-to-reach areas, with current spike of COVID-19 cases compounded by already poor health governance and health access systems in Myanmar.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To strengthen community awareness of and demand for services to address Emergency Health, Protection and Nutrition needs in order to reduce the risk and community vulnerabilities stemming from COVID-19 and strengthen resilience for the future.
To strengthen community preparedness and response to emergencies through community-led Action Plans, an Early Warning System (EWS) and improved collaboration between the key stakeholders involved in mitigating and managing emergencies.   
To support recovery of livelihoods after COVID-19 and to increase business capacity and access to financial and livelihoods support.</narrative>
  </description>
